<item>
            <title>[LU-12400] Support for linux kernel version 5.2</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12400</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Support for building lustre / &lt;del&gt;ldiskfs&lt;/del&gt; with current upstream kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added iov_iter_type needed to iterate over iovec&lt;br/&gt;
 vm_fault_t used for (some) vm_operations_struct handlers&lt;br/&gt;
 SunRPC cache hash lock is now a spinlock_t, readers are now all RCU&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;ldiskfs:&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;del&gt;__ext4_find_entry became a helper function for ext4_find_entry&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;del&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;breaking a few ldiskfs patches&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Multi-page bvec has landed, use bvec_iter_all&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;extfs_dirhash now requires a directory (for case-insensitive directories).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ib_sg_dma_address() and ib_sg_dma_len() are removed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With CONFIG_ARCH_STACKWALK stack_trace_save_tsk() is not exported.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;y2038:&#160;SO_SNDTIMEO, SO_RCVTIMEO removed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;legacy &apos;get_ds()&apos; function is removed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use the new vm_fault_t type (optional)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
